  "text": "Researchers using data from European (football) soccer also concluded that bookmakers account for bettor sentiment, in terms of the popularity of certain teams or countries. showed that more favorable odds are offered on weekend matches. The authors attributed this difference to the amount of casual bettors participating in the betting market for weekend games compared to weekend games. Finally, [CITATION_1] examined the sentiment from national football club matches across Europe. Using data from football matches from across Europe, [CITATION_2] found evidence of biases in the prices that bookmakers offer for a country's national football clubs. They explained their result as perception bias, the confidence of the bettors that their home country will win, and loyalty bias, wagers strictly on the national team to win due to the loyalty of bettors.",
